message.content:
Grocery stores are establishments primarily engaged in retailing a wide variety of food products, including fresh fruits, vegetables, dairy products, baked goods, meats and poultry. In addition to perishable items like produce and meat, they also sell non-perishable household products such as canned foods, dried grains/pastas/beans/tuna packaged snacks/beverages cleaning or decor items/Pets food/etc.

Supermarkets are large self-service stores that sell groceries as well as other product lines like clothing accessories/cosmetics/kitchen appliances/small electronics/household objects/shoes/books etc., depending on the country's habits.

These two terms may be used interchangeably at times due to their similarities in function; however grocery store's main focus is on selling basic necessary items for everyday use while supermarket provides assorted range of both functional and life-style based luxuries catering every need smaller according population age demographics / economic levels .
